  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "OECD Composite Consumer Confidence for the United States (USACSCICP02STSAM). Monthly survey-based measure of household sentiment, expressed as percentage balance (net positive minus negative responses). Tracks similar cyclical turning points as the Conference Board CCI.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Baumohl #7 proxy. Expectations lead spending. Sharp drops historically precede risk-off moves. Freely available on FRED, updated monthly.\n",
    "scoring_rule": "Level + MoM change. Phase 3."
  },
